cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper is about benchmarking graph database systems using the LDBC SNB benchmark, which is a benchmark for social network data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.CY (computers and society).
